HEADWORD: Noctilucin
<hw>Noc*ti*lu"cin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A fatlike substance in certain marine animals, to which they owe
their phosphorescent properties.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Noctilucine</ent>⟦br⟧
